No, you aren't supposed to have to ream them.  It you get a new links set, 
they come with the pin in the needle bearing in the bushing.   You are warned 
that each set is a set, so don't go swapping pieces around, like you don't mix 
and match cases halves.   

Sounds odd, I'd call up the place you got them from.

